cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper proposes a programmable deep learning architecture template (VTA) that is designed to be extensible in the face of evolving workloads. It also proposes a flow that performs design space exploration to generate a customized hardware architecture and software operator library. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper focuses on deep learning acceleration for object classification and style transfer, which are common tasks in AI. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a runtime system equipped with a JIT compiler for flexible code-generation and heterogeneous execution, which is relevant to systems and control. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper deploys optimized deep learning models for object classification and style transfer, which are tasks in computer vision. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes a two-level ISA and a JIT compiler, which are relevant to programming languages.
